      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOOKED ON JOY (5) was never in contention last time after missing the jump at this track, but prior to that won by 2.25 lengths at this track (22.81) beating Aussie Rattler in a Grade 5 on March 28. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. SPARKY KEY (2) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at this track over 400m behind Nakita Moira (23.86) in a Grade 5. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Worth another chance. KAREN STRATUS (7) is generally an honest type in the frame at six of 17 starts but missed the placings last time when fifth (15.99) over 272m at this track. Has a good record here including three wins. Looks suited and expected to run well. CRANKY CRUISER (1) was unplaced here last start but gets her chance to atone.",
